title: 1991–92 in Scottish football
text:
The 1991–92 season was the 95th season of competitive <a href="Association%20football">football</a> in Scotland.
Scottish Premier Division.
Champions: Rangers
Relegated: St Mirren, Dunfermline Athletic
Scottish League Division One.
Promoted: Dundee, Partick Thistle
Relegated: Montrose, Forfar Athletic
Scottish League Division Two.
Promoted: Dumbarton, Cowdenbeath
Scotland national team.
